      content: '"Healthcare data is a goldmine buried under decades of technical debt. The average health system runs 1,300 different applications. Most can\'t even share data with each other. Enter FHIR — Fast Healthcare Interoperability Resources — the standard that\'s finally connecting the dots. Epic, Cerner, all major EHRs now support it. Predictive analytics is the game-changer. Kaiser Permanente\'s early warning system reduced sepsis mortality by 60%. Optum\'s predictive models identify patients likely to become high-cost 12 months BEFORE it happens. Intermountain Healthcare built a real-time dashboard that tracks cost, quality, and utilization across every value-based contract. Their analytics team identified $300 million in savings opportunities in ONE year. But here\'s the real talk: 70% of healthcare AI projects fail. Not because of bad algorithms — because of bad data. Garbage in, garbage out."',
